<list list-type="bullet"><list-item><p>Provide educational materials and discuss the health-behaviour link, enabling patients to understand why and how they make lifestyle changes.</p></list-item><list-item><p>Provide educational materials and risk information on the consequences of AF and treatment with/or without warfarin</p></list-item><list-item><p>Provide opportunities for social comparison with other patients</p></list-item><list-item><p>Encourage patients to self-monitor, create action plans, and use their own memory aids/cues for remembering to take tablets</p></list-item><list-item><p>Discuss patients concerns and barriers to changing their lifestyle and adopting a new treatment regime; correct any misconceptions with accurate information.</p></list-item></list></p><p>Presenting the full methodology behind the development of interventions could enable intervention design to become a much more efficient and transparent process.</p></sec></sec></body><back><ack><title>Acknowledgments</title><p>We would like to thank all of the patients who took part in the development of this intervention and the randomised controlled trial to test the intervention. Danielle E. Clarkesmith&#x02019;s PhD studentship to conduct the TREAT study was partly funded by the Investigator-initiated educational grant awarded to Deirdre A. Lane by Bayer Healthcare. </p></ack><app-group><app id="app1-healthcare-04-00010"><title>Supplementary Materials</title><supplementary-material content-type="local-data" id="healthcare-04-00010-s001"><media xlink:href="healthcare-04-00010-s001.pdf"><caption><p>Click here for additional data file.</p></caption></media></supplementary-material><p>Supplementary Figures S1&#x02013;S4 are available online at <uri xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://www.mdpi.com/2227-9032/4/1/10/s1">http://www.mdpi.com/2227-9032/4/1/10/s1</uri>.</p></app></app-group><notes><title>Author Contributions</title><p>All authors conceived and designed the study; Danielle E. Clarkesmith, Christian Borg Xuereb, and Deirdre A. Lane performed the focus groups; all authors analysed the data; Danielle E. Clarkesmith, Helen M. Pattison, and Deirdre A. Lane wrote the paper and all authors provided critical revision. </p></notes><notes><title>Conflicts of Interest</title><p>Danielle E. Clarkesmith: The intervention development and randomised controlled trial to test the TREAT intervention was partly funded by the Investigator-initiated educational grant awarded to Deirdre A. Lane by Bayer Healthcare. The funder had no influence over the design, data collection or reporting of this study. Deirdre A. Lane: has received investigator-initiated educational grants from Bayer Healthcare, Boehringer Ingelheim and Bristol-Myers-Squibb and has served as a speaker for Boehringer Ingelheim, Bayer Healthcare, and BMS/Pfizer. She is a member of the Steering Committee for the AEGEAN study, a Phase IV trial with apixaban. Helen M. Pattison: No conflicts of interest to declare. Christian Borg Xuereb: No conflicts of interest to declare.</p></notes><ref-list><title>References</title><ref id="B1-healthcare-04-00010"><label>1.</label><element-citation publication-type="journal">
